text: Jean-François Voguet (8 August 1949 - 2 February 2021) was a French politician. He was a member of the Senate of France, representing the Val-de- Marne department. He was a member of the Communist, Republican, and Citizen Group. Voguet died from COVID-19 during the COVID-19 pandemic in France on 2 February 2021, aged 71.Fontenay-sous-Bois: hommage à Jean-François Voguet ce midi ==References== ==Other websites== * Page on the Senate website Category:1949 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Politicians from Île-de- France Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in France Category:People from Val-de-Marne
